<% content_for :title, "Terms of Service — LocalBaker" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "LocalBaker Terms of Service — plain-English rules for bakers and customers." %>

<div class="stack-lg">
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>

  <div class="stack">
    <p><small>Last updated: <%= Date.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %>. We are not lawyers. This is a starting point — review with one before relying on it.</small></p>

    <h2>What LocalBaker is</h2>
    <p>LocalBaker is software that lets home bakers post upcoming bakes and lets customers reserve them. We are not a party to any sale. The baker bakes the food. The customer pays the baker.</p>

    <h2>Your account</h2>
    <p>You're responsible for the email address you sign up with and for keeping your sign-in link secret. Tell us if you think someone else has gained access.</p>

    <h2>What you post</h2>
    <p>If you're a baker, you own the content you post (product names, photos, descriptions). You give us permission to display it on your storefront and in directory listings. Don't post anything you don't have rights to.</p>

    <h2>Payments</h2>
    <p>LocalBaker subscription fees are processed by Stripe. We don't store your full card number. If we add customer-facing payments later, we'll update this page first.</p>

    <h2>Food safety</h2>
    <p>Bakers are responsible for following local cottage food laws and food safety practices. LocalBaker is not a regulator and does not inspect kitchens.</p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>The service is provided as-is. We do our best to keep it running, but we don't promise it will be available 100% of the time. We are not liable for losses caused by service downtime, customer no-shows, allergic reactions, or anything else outside our reasonable control.</p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>You can delete your account at any time from <%= link_to "settings", settings_account_path %>. We can suspend accounts that break these terms or local laws.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update these terms. Significant changes will be noted on this page with a new "last updated" date.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p><%= link_to "Get in touch", new_contact_path %> if anything's unclear.</p>
  </div>
</div>
